-- Lithuania Weighs Energy, Real Estate Initial Public Offerings, FT Reports
-- Ben Martin
-- 2010-07-08T00:43:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/lithuania-weighs-energy-real-estate-initial-public-offerings-ft-reports.html

          
          
             Lithuania is considering initial
public offerings of state-owned energy and real estate companies
in an attempt to attract private capital, the Financial Times
reported, citing Prime Minister  Andrius Kubilius .  
 “Energy will be the first priority” because the country’s
large investment projects require capital, Kubilius said, the
newspaper reported.  
